description: From Middle English semblen, from Old French sembler (“to resemble”).

verbs.description: semble (third-person singular simple present sembles, present participle sembling, simple past and past participle sembled)

entries.meaning: (obsolete) To imitate; to make a representation or likeness.
examples: Where sembling art may carve the fair effect.

entries.meaning: (law, third-person singular only) It seems; it appears that

description: From Middle English semble, from Old French semble.

examples: name and deede that bare the semble stile
